# React/Next.js Templates

## Syntax Rules
- Use functional components with clear props interfaces
- Prefer TypeScript in new components (`.tsx`)
- Keep components small and composable; split complex blocks into child components

## Forms
- Use shared form components and schema-based validation (e.g. Zod + React Hook Form)
- Keep client-side validation aligned with backend validation rules
- Never trust client-side validation alone for security-critical constraints

## Component Patterns
- Place reusable UI in `components/` and feature-specific UI near feature routes
- Use semantic HTML and accessible labels/roles for all interactive controls
- Keep side effects in hooks (`useEffect`) and avoid data-fetching in deep child nodes

## Data Fetching
- In Next.js, prefer Server Components/route handlers for initial data
- For client updates, use React Query/SWR with stable query keys
- Handle loading, empty, and error states explicitly in UI

## Routing
- Use Next.js App Router conventions (`app/`), nested layouts where useful
- Keep route segment names meaningful and URL-safe
- Separate public vs authenticated areas with dedicated layouts/middleware

## i18n
- Use translation keys, never hardcode product copy in components
- Keep key naming consistent and hierarchical (`feature.section.label`)

## Styling
- Prefer Tailwind utility classes + shared primitives
- Avoid one-off inline styles except for dynamic computed values
